==First bikes== [[Image:Yamaha YA-1 00.jpg|thumb|right|Yamaha YA-1]] <!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:Yamaha YC1.jpg|thumb|right|Yamaha YC-1]] --> *[[Yamaha YA-1|YA-1]] built August 1954, produced January 1955. The first bike manufactured by Yamaha; it had an [[air-cooled engine|air-cooled]], [[two-stroke engine|two-stroke]], [[single cylinder engine|single cylinder]] 125&nbsp;cc engine<ref name=starhistory>http://www.starmotorcycles.com/star/company/historyhome/home.aspx</ref> *[[Yamaha YC-1|YC-1]] (1956) was the second bike manufactured by Yamaha; it was a 175&nbsp;cc single cylinder two-stroke.<ref name=starhistory/> *[[Yamaha YD-1|YD-1]] (1957) Yamaha began production of its first 250&nbsp;cc, two-stroke twin, the YD1.<ref name=starhistory/> *[[Yamaha MF-1|MF-1]] (1958) 50&nbsp;cc, two-stroke, single cylinder, step through street bike<ref name=starhistory/> *[[Yamaha DT-1|DT-1]] (1968) Yamaha's first true off-road motorcycle.<ref name=starhistory/> *[[Yamaha XS 650|XS-1]] (1970) Yamaha's first four-stroke engine motorcycle (650&nbsp;cc twin).<ref name=yamhistory>http://www.yamaha-motor.com/corporate/historytimeline.aspx, Yamaha website timeline, accessed October 2, 2011</ref> * Yamaha YZ Monocross (1975) First production motocross bike with a single rear shock.<ref name=yamhistory/> * [[Yamaha YZ450F#First Generation: YZ400F - 1998-2000|Yamaha YZ400F]] (1998) First mass produced four-stroke motocross motorcycle.<ref name=yamhistory/>
